      "writtenOn": "2021-03-02T15:34:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This technically reduces the maximum key size by a factor of 8, but still allows for keys that are 2^13 (8k) in size, which seems like plenty. I also think we should reorganize how we build processor keys here in a follow-up.\n\nAdding the size of the key to the key is a strange pattern. The FP code also adds things in a strange order, so children are emitted mostly (but not entirely) before their parents. If each FP just emitted \"how many children do I have\" first, I think we could remove the size meta-data, and do things in a more consistent top-down order, with all data for one FP fully contiguous.",
      "revId": "224b72c0a4cc1d91cfd18a01f71bd5e945df54b2",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
